20to%20restrain%20many%20of%20Trump's%20personal%20instincts.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3E%26quot%3BI%20was%20surprised%20by%20the%20level%20of%20Kelly's%20distress%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BHe%20clearly%20suffered%20from%20political%20shell%20shock.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EFormer%20Rep.%20Adam%20Kinzinger%20said%20former%20Trump%20White%20House%20chief%20of%20staff%20John%20Kelly%20was%20once%20so%20%26quot%3Bexhausted%26quot%3B%20from%20his%20role%20that%20he%20%26quot%3Bcould%20barely%20stay%20awake%26quot%3B%20during%20a%20private%20breakfast%20at%201600%20Pennsylvania%20Avenue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKinzinger%20made%20the%20revelation%20in%20his%20newly-released%20book%2C%20%26quot%3BRenegade%2C%26quot%3B%20where%20he%20spoke%20of%20the%20internal%20pressures%20that%20the%20retired%20Marine%20Corps%20general%20and%20former%20Homeland%20Security%20secretary%20faced%20as%20he%20sought%20to%20bring%20a%20sense%20of%20stability%20to%20a%20White%20House%20that%20was%20often%20guided%20more%20by%20Trump's%20personal%20whims%20than%20the%20counsel%20of%20top%20advisors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20former%20Republican%20lawmaker%20in%20his%20book%20detailed%20how%20Kelly%20arrived%20to%20the%20breakfast%20%26quot%3Blooking%20gaunt%20and%20exhausted%26quot%3B%20as%20he%20intended%20to%20update%20five%20GOP%20lawmakers%20on%20developments%20in%20Afghanistan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%208%3A00%20a.m.%20and%20he%20could%20barely%20stay%20awake%2C%26quot%3B%20Kinzinger%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BHe%20told%20us%20he%20was%20trying%20as%20hard%20as%20he%20could%20but%20was%20'barely%20holding%20it%20together.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20was%20surprised%20by%20the%20level%20of%20Kelly's%20distress%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20continued.%20%26quot%3BHe%20clearly%20suffered%20from%20political%20shell%20shock.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKelly%20served%20as%20chief%20of%20staff%20from%20July%202017%20through%20January%202019%2C%20and%20Kinzinger%20in%20the%20book%20stated%20that%20the%20breakfast%20occurred%20sometime%20during%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20retired%20general's%20tenure%20at%20the%20White%20House.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKinzinger%20said%20that%20Kelly%20was%20intended%20to%20be%20a%20moderating%20force%20in%20the%20administration%2C%20but%20had%20to%20exert%20energy%20to%20combat%20Trump's%20preference%20to%20trust%20his%20own%20judgment%20or%20the%20views%20of%20those%20fully%20aligned%20with%20him%2C%20which%20the%20former%20congressman%20said%20was%20a%20goal%20that%20Kelly%20pursued%20%26quot%3Bin%20vain.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20problem%20with%20Trump%2C%20from%20a%20chief%20of%20staff's%20perspective%2C%20was%20that%20he%20preferred%20to%20do%20everything%20informally%20and%20on%20his%20own%20with%20minimum%20staff%20engagement%2C%26quot%3B%20Kinzinger%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BConsequently%2C%20Kelly%20and%20others%20regularly%20discovered%20that%20Trump%20had%20considered%20advice%20from%20this%20crony%20or%20that%20social%20contact%20at%20his%20Mar-a-Lago%20resort%20and%20was%20serious%20about%20acting%20on%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20work%20of%20diverting%20Trump's%20attention%20away%20from%20terrible%20ideas%20and%20directing%20him%20to%20fulfill%20his%20duties%20obviously%20took%20all%20of%20Kelly's%20energy%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20October%2C%20Kelly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnn.com%2F2023%2F10%2F02%2Fpolitics%2Fjohn-kelly-donald-trump-us-service-members-veterans%2Findex.html%5C%22%3Ein%20a%20CNN%20statement%3C%2Fa%3E%20confirmed%20several%20claims%20from%20a%20damning%202020%20piece%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theatlantic.com%2Fpolitics%2Farchive%2F2020%2F09%2Ftrump-americans-who-died-at-war-are-losers-and-suckers%2F615997%2F%5C%22%3Epublished%20by%20The%20Atlantic%3C%2Fa%3E%20which%20alleged%20that%20Trump%20had%20called%20fallen%20US%20veterans%20%26quot%3Bsuckers%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Blosers%26quot%3B%20for%20having