F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwho-is-mike-johnson-republican-speaker-house-louisiana-2023-10%5C%22%3Enow%20led%20by%20a%20Ukraine%20skeptic.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20effort%20to%20avoid%20those%20dynamics%20altogether%2C%20Republican%20Sen.%20Roger%20Marshall%20of%20Kansas%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.marshall.senate.gov%2Fnewsroom%2Fpress-releases%2Fsenators-marshall-vance-lee-and-cruz-introduce-legislation-to-give-immediate-assistance-and-aid-to-israel%2F%5C%22%3Eintroduced%20a%20bill%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20week%20that%20would%20essentially%20give%20most%20Democrats%20an%20offer%20they%20can't%20refuse%3A%20the%20entire%20%2414.3%20billion%20that%20the%20Biden%20administration%20wants%20for%20Israel%2C%20no%20strings%20or%20poison%20pills%20attached.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Marshall%20and%20his%20three%20Republican%20co-sponsors%20couldn't%20force%20a%20vote%20on%20this%20themselves%20in%20the%20Democratic-controlled%20Senate%2C%20it%20made%20for%20a%20solid%20blueprint%20that%20the%20House%20could%20have%20used.%20It%20would've%20been%20passed%20the%20House%20by%20an%20overwhelming%20bipartisan%20vote%20and%20applied%20significant%20pressure%20to%20senators%20who%20want%20to%20keep%20Israel%20aid%20linked%20with%20Ukraine%20aid.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEnter%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwho-is-mike-johnson-republican-speaker-house-louisiana-2023-10%5C%22%3Ebrand-new%20speaker%20of%20the%20House.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHouse%20Speaker%20Mike%20Johnson%20is%20teeing%20up%20a%20vote%20this%20week%20on%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Frules.house.gov%2Fsites%2Frepublicans.rules118.house.gov%2Ffiles%2FISRAELFINAL_xml.pdf%5C%22%3Ebill%20that%20does%20the%20same%20thing%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20Marshall's%2C%20but%20with%20a%20catch%20%E2%80%94%20it%20also%20rescinds%20%2414.3%20billion%20in%20funds%20provided%20to%20the%20Internal%20Revenue%20Service%20by%20the%20Inflation%20Reduction%20Act.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20offsetting%20the%20cost%20is%20likely%20to%20satisfy%20the%20often-restive%20fiscal%20hawks%20in%20his%20conference%2C%20the%20bill%20as%20written%20is%20a%20total%20non-starter%20for%20almost%20every%20Democrat%20in%20both%20the%20House%20and%20Senate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20Democrats%20are%20having%20no%20problem%20arguing%20that%20it's%20a%20%26quot%3Bpoison%20pill%2C%26quot%3B%20pointing%20to%20the%20fact%20that%20IRS%20funding%20cuts%20would%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.crfb.org%2Fblogs%2Firs-rescission-would-worsen-deficits%5C%22%3Elikely%20increase%20the%20annual%20deficit%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20weakening%20the%20agency's%20ability%20to%20collect%20revenue%20for%20the%20US%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTheir%20price%20for%20helping%20Israel%20and%20abandoning%20America's%20responsibilities%20around%20the%20globe%3F%20Making%20it%20much%20easier%20for%20the%20ultra-rich%20to%20cheat%20on%20their%20taxes%2C%26quot%3B%20Senate%20Majority%20Leader%20Chuck%20Schumer%20told%20reporters%20on%20Tuesday.%20%26quot%3BHow%20the%20heck%20could%20that%20be%20their%20highest%20priority%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Senate%20Minority%20Leader%20Mitch%20McConnell%20and%20a%20sizable%20portion%20of%20the%20Senate%20GOP%20actually%20support%20the%20Biden%20administration's%20approach%20of%20pairing%20Ukraine%20and%20Israel%20aid%2C%20and%20McConnell%20is%20taking%20a%20dim%20view%20of%20Johnson's%20bill%2C%20suggesting%20that%20it%20may%20not%20even%20pass%20the%20House.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe'll%20see%20if%20the%20bill%20comes%20out%20of%20the%20House%20%E2%80%94%20and%20if%20so%2C%20what%20kind%20of%20margin%20it%20has%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Kentucky%20Republican%20told%20reporters%20on%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Republicans%20who%20hoped%20to%20split%20Israel%20and%20Ukraine%20already%20represented%20a%20minority%20of%20the%20party%2C%20at%20least%20in%20the%20upper%20chamber.%20By%20writing%20the%20bill%20the%20way%20he%20did%2C%20Johnson%20is%20only%20further%20weakening%20that%20conservative%20faction's%20hand%20%E2%80%94%20though%20only%20some%20of%20them%20will%20readily%20admit%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYes%2C%26quot%3B%20Marshall%20said%20when%20Insider%20asked%20whether%20Johnson's%20bill%20made%20it%20harder%20for%20them%20to%20pursue%20their%20existing%20strategy.%20%26quot%3BBut%20my%20ultimate%20goal%20here%2C%20regardless%20of%20all%20these%20parliamentarian%20maneuvers%2C%20is%20to%20get%20funding%20for%20Israel%20as%20soon%20as%20possible.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESen.%20Ted%20Cruz%20of%20Texas%2C%20one%20of%20three%20Republican%20co-sponsors%20on%20Marshall's%20bill%2C%20struck%20a%20similar%20tone%2C%20falling%20back%20into%20a%20partisan%20messaging%20stance%20when%20asked%20if%20Republicans%20were%20missing%20an%20opportunity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDemocrats%20can%20complain%20about%20the%20%5BIRS%20cuts%5D%20if%20they%20want%20to%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Cruz.%20%26quot%3BIt%20wouldn't%20be%20the%20first%20time%20Democrats%20put%20partisan%20politics%20above%20doing%20the%20right%20thing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESen.%20Josh%20Hawley%20of%20Missouri%20said%20he%20didn't%20want%20to%20%26quot%3Bplay%20pundit%20on%20the%20House%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20he'd%20%26quot%3Blove%20to%20cut%20the%20IRS%20regardless%20of%20anything%2C%20and%20if%20we%20can%20use%20that%20money%20to%20help%20Israel%2C%20best%20of%20all%20worlds.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20Sen.%20JD%20Vance%20of%20Ohio%2C%20another%20Republican%20co-sponsor%20on%20Marshall's%20bill%2C%20suggested%20that%20Johnson's%20bill%20may%20just%20be%20a%20starting%20point.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTo%20get%20Senate%20Democrats%20on%20it%2C%20is%20it%20going%20to%20look%20exactly%20what%20it%20looks%20like%20in%20the%20House%3F%20I%20don't%20know%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Vance.%20%26quot%3BBut%20I%20think%20that%20at%20least%20gives%20us%20a%20vehicle%20to%20try%20to%20get%20this%20thing%20done.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPerhaps%20Republicans%20simply%20aren't%20interested%20in%20saying%20anything%20bad%20about%20Johnson%20%E2%80%94%20after%20all%2C%20he's%20their%20party's%20brand%20new%20House%20speaker%2C%20and%20it%20took%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjim-jordan-speaker-house-stalled-austin-scott-2023-10%5C%22%3Epainful%20and%20embarrassing%20three%20weeks%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20get%20a%20speaker%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20got%20to%20realize%20that%20the%20speaker%20of%20the%20Republican-controlled%20House%20is%20the%20leader%20of%20the%20party%2C%26quot%3B%20Sen.%20Ron%20Johnson%20of%20Wisconsin%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Figorbobic%2Fstatus%2F1719380006042738845%5C%22%3Etold%20reporters%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Tuesday.%20%26quot%3BHe's%20making%20some%20calls%2C%20and%20we%20in%20the%20minority%20of%20the%20Senate%20ought%20to%20follow%20his%20lead%2C%20and%20not%20undermine%20him.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENonetheless%2C%20Johnson's%20bill%20makes%20it%20only%20more%20likely%20that%20anti-Ukraine%20aid%20Republicans%20get%20rolled.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20House%20passes%20his%20bill%2C%20the%20Senate%20will%20not%20pass%20it%2C%20at%20least%20in%20its%20current%20form.%20Without%20the%20pressure%20of%20an%20acceptable%20standalone%20Israel%20aid%20bill%2C%20senators%20will%20be%20content%20to%20continue%20hammering%20out%20a%20bill%20that%20roughly%20matches%20the%20Biden%20administration's%20requests%2C%20eventually%20passing%20it%20and%20likely%20forcing%20the%20House%20to%20swallow%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20what%20Democrats%20consider%20to%20be%20a%20%26quot%3Bpoison%20pill%26quot%3B%20may%20just%20be%20the%20cost%20of%20doing%20business%20in%20today's%20GOP-run%20House.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe's%20trying%20to%20hold%20his%20conference%20together%2C%20I%20think%20rightfully%20so%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Vance.%20%26quot%3BI%20mean%2C%20the%20counter-argument%20is%2C%20if%20he%20doesn't%20include%20%5Bspending%20cuts%5D%2C%20it's%20not%20even%20going%20to%20pass%20the%20House.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmike-johnson-israel-aid-ukraine-irs-cuts-senate-republicans-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698783115000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65413aee3cc84b4dfaf8a02a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmike-johnson-israel-aid-ukraine-irs-cuts-senate-republicans-2023-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Republicans%20had%20a%20strong%20strategy%20to%20force%20Democrats%20to%20separate%20Israel%20and%20Ukraine%20aid.%20Then%20the%20new%20House%20Speaker%20threw%20in%20a%20major%20poison%20pill.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22bmetzger%40insider.com%20(Bryan%20Metzger)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A20%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmike-johnson-israel-aid-ukraine-irs-cuts-senate-republicans-2023-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20top%20GOP%20lawmaker%20is%20taking%20legal%20action%20to%20scrutinize%20the%20Education%20Department's%20authority%20to%20cancel%20student%20debt%20for%20defrauded%20borrowers%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224381%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Rep.%20Virginia%20Foxx%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F62ebcc6659282400185a5f86%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222921%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERep.%20Virginia%20Foxx%2C%20R-N.C.%2C%20speaks%20during%20a%20news%20conference%20with%20other%20House%20Republican%20members%20in%20Washington%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20March%209%2C%202021.%3Cp%3ECaroline%20Brehman%2FCQ-Roll%20Call%2C%20Inc%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EGOP%20Rep.%20Virginia%20Foxx%20issued%20a%20subpoena%20to%20the%20Education%20Department%20on%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20subpoena%20requested%20a%20range%20of%20documents%20relating%20to%20the%20department's%20borrower%20defense%20actions.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EFoxx%20said%20the%20department%20has%20failed%20to%20provide%20information%20on%20its%20authority%20for%20that%20debt%20relief.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20top%20Republican%20lawmaker%20is%20turning%20to%20legal%20action%20to%20get%20answers%20from%20the%20Education%20Department%20on%20student-debt%20relief.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Tuesday%2C%20Chair%20of%20the%20House%20education%20committee%20Virginia%20Foxx%20issued%20a%20subpoena%20to%20Education%20Secretary%20Miguel%20Cardona%20to%20get%20information%20on%20the%20Education%20Department's%20relief%20through%20borrower%20defense%20to%20repayment.%20Borrower%20defense%20claims%20are%20forms%20a%20borrower%20can%20submit%20if%20they%20believe%20they%20were%20defrauded%20by%20the%20school%20they%20attended%2C%20and%20if%20approved%2C%20their%20loans%20from%20that%20school%20would%20be%20discharged.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFoxx%20isn't%20convinced%20of%20the%20department's%20authority%20to%20grant%20that%20relief.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20wrote%20in%20her%20subpoena%20cover%20letter%20%E2%80%94%20first%20reviewed%20by%20Insider%20%E2%80%94%20that%20beginning%20in%20May%202023%2C%20she%20submitted%20requests%20to%20the%20department%20for%20information%20on%20the%20actions%20it%20has%20taken%20to%20approve%20debt%20discharged%20through%20borrower%20defense%2C%20and%20she%20has%20yet%20to%20receive%20the%20requested%20documents.%20The%20department%20instead%20said%20that%20the%20Government%20Accountability%20Office%20has%20to%20first%20complete%20its%20own%20investigation%20on%20borrower%20defense.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20the%20first%20time%20the%20Committee%20has%20subpoenaed%20the%20Education%20Department%2C%20and%20it%20is%20a%20measure%20that%20I%20do%20not%20take%20lightly.%20Secretary%20Cardona%20sat%20before%20this%20Committee%20in%20May%20and%20gave%20us%20his%20word%20that%20he%20would%20assist%20us%20in%20our%20oversight%20efforts%2C%26quot%3B%20Foxx%20told%20Insider%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BClearly%2C%20Secretary%20Cardona's%20word%20doesn't%20mean%20much%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BHis%20lack%20of%20candor%20not%20only%20blocks%20the%20Committee%20from%20doing%20its%20job%2C%20but%20it%20also%20leaves%20students%2C%20borrowers%2C%20and%20institutions%20in%20the%20dark.%20We%20intend%20to%20get%20the%20answers%20for%20the%20American%20people.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20Education%20Department%20spokesperson%20told%20Insider%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20Department%20is%20unapologetically%20proud%20of%20our%20efforts%20to%20fix%20borrower%20defense%20that%20have%20helped%20nearly%201.1%20million%20students%20get%20%2414.8%20billion%20in%20relief%20from%20notorious%20predatory%20institutions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhile%20Congressional%20Republican%20Leadership%20of%20the%20Education%20and%20Workforce%20Committee%20stand%20by%20these%20predatory%20colleges%2C%20the%20Department%20has%20the%20backs%20of%20borrowers%20who%20were%20taken%20advantage%20of%20and%20will%20continue%20to%20hold%20colleges%20accountable%20for%20their%20illegal%20actions%20toward%20students%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20spokesperson%20added.%20%26quot%3BThe%20Department%20has%20already%20been%20responsive%20to%20the%20Committee's%20requests%20and%20this%20escalatory%20action%20is%20inappropriate.%20Despite%20this%20political%20stunt%2C%20we%20remain%20committed%20to%20cooperating%20with%20Congress%20in%20good%20faith.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFoxx's%20first%20request%20for%20information%20was%20on%20May%2024%2C%20regarding%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsupreme-court-upholds-student-loan-debt-cancellation-defrauded-borrowers-settlement-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%246%20billion%20in%20relief%20for%20200%2C000%20borrowers%3C%2Fa%3E%20through%20a%20settlement%2C%20Sweet%20v.%20Cardona.%20While%20the%20lawsuit%20originated%20under%20former%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20over%20stalled%20borrower%20defense%20claims%2C%20it%20was%20not%20resolved%20under%20his%20administration%2C%20leaving%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F200k-student-loan-borrowers-defrauded-debt-canceled-settlement-biden-cardona-2022-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECardona%20to%20agree%20to%20the%20settlement%20last%20year%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20settlement%20led%20to%20a%20group%20discharge%20for%20impacted%20borrowers%2C%20rather%20than%20going%20through%20each%20borrowers'%20claims%20individually%2C%20which%20Foxx%20said%20raised%20questions%20about%20the%20department's%20authority.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20subpoena%20sent%20on%20Tuesday%20requests%20a%20range%20of%20documents%20by%20November%2014%20including%20any%20communications%20related%20to%20the%20Sweet%20v.%20Cardona%20settlement%2C%20documents%20describing%20the%20legal%20authority%20for%20borrower%20defense%20claims%2C%20and%20the%20number%20of%20borrowers%20who%20received%20relief%20under%20Cardona%20through%20borrower%20defense.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBiden's%20Education%20Department%20has%20consistently%20stood%20by%20its%20legal%20authority%20to%20approve%20borrower%20defense%20claims%20for%20defrauded%20borrowers.%20In%20October%202022%2C%20it%20released%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmake-student-debt-payments-cheaper-fix-loan-forgiveness-biden-plans-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enew%20regulations%20to%20streamline%20the%20borrower%20defense%20process%20%3C%2Fa%3Eby%20allowing%20borrowers%20to%20file%20claims%20individually%20or%20as%20a%20group.%20It%20also%20lays%20out%20a%20process%20for%20a%20department%20to%20recoup%20funds%20from%20a%20school%20over%20approved%20claims.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20regulations%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.federalregister.gov%2Fdocuments%2F2022%2F1