0ex-Dallas%20Fed%20Chair%20says.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EThe%20US%20is%20borrowing%20this%20quarter%20will%20amount%20%248.66%20billion%20dollars%20a%20day.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EThat's%20a%20%26quot%3Bhorrendously%26quot%3B%20large%20number%2C%20Fisher%20said%2C%20and%20it's%20set%20to%20grow%20next%20year.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20higher%20for%20longer%20outlook%20for%20interest%20rates%20sparked%20a%20historic%20crash%20in%20Treasury%20bonds%20this%20month%2C%20but%20there's%20another%20factor%20that's%20set%20to%20keep%20yields%20higher%20going%20forward%2C%20and%20that's%20US%20fiscal%20policy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20former%20Dallas%20Federal%20Reserve%20President%20Richard%20Fisher%2C%20massive%20government%20borrowing%20needed%20to%20fund%20massive%20spending%20will%20be%20a%20culprit%20of%20higher%20bond%20yields.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20believe%20what's%20driving%20rates%20higher%20and%20what%20will%20keep%20them%20higher%20for%20longer%20is%20our%20fiscal%20policy%2C%26quot%3B%20Fisher%20told%20CNBC%20on%20Tuesday.%20%26quot%3BThe%20daily%20borrowing%20for%20the%20next%2090%20days%20as%20we%20go%20into%20the%20last%20quarter%20of%20the%20US%20government%20is%20%248.66%20billion%20a%20day.%20A%20day.%20These%20numbers%20have%20gotten%20horrendously%20large.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20just%20no%20way%20you%20can%20clear%20this%20market%20that%20is%20so%20heavily%20dependent%20on%20more%20issuance%2C%20more%20issuance%2C%20more%20issuance%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20mounting%20pile%20of%20US%20debt%20is%20an%20increasingly%20worrying%20factor%20for%20investors%20who%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fbonds%2Ftreasury-bond-auctions-fail-ballooning-federal-deficit-us-debt-rates-2023-10%5C%22%3Eafraid%20of%20what%20the%20soaring%20deficit%3C%2Fa%3E%20means%20for%20the%20long%20term%20stability%20of%20the%20US%20economy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompounding%20the%20issue%20of%20soaring%20debt%20is%20rising%20interest%20rates%2C%20as%20borrowing%20costs%20rocket%20higher%20amid%20the%20Federal%20Reserve's%20fight%20against%20inflation.%20On%20top%20of%20that%2C%20the%20Treasury%20is%20issuing%20more%20bonds%20at%20a%20time%20when%20the%20field%20of%20potential%20buyers%20is%20potentially%20smaller%2C%20another%20factor%20that%20could%20weigh%20on%20prices%20and%20keep%20yields%20up.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20the%20Fed's%20in%20good%20shape%20here%2C%20it%20is%20not%20the%20Fed%20that%20is%20the%20problem%2C%26quot%3B%20Fisher%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20the%20fiscal%20authorities%20that%20are%20out%20of%20control.%20And%20as%20long%20as%20that's%20the%20case%2C%20we're%20going%20to%20live%20in%20a%205%25%20world.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESupply%20is%20not%20often%20a%20major%20concern%20for%20Treasurys%2C%20which%20represent%20the%20world's%20biggest%20and%20most%20liquid%20securities%20market.%20However%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fbonds%2Fbond-market-outlook-treasury-selloff-rising-yields-g7-debt-supply-2023-10%5C%22%3ET.%20Rowe%20Price's%20chief%20Europe%20economist%20said%20recently%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20market%20is%20entering%20a%20new%20world%20where%20supply%20is%20indeed%20a%20concern.%20That's%20because%20the%20biggest%20buyers%20of%20the%20bonds%E2%80%94central%20banks%E2%80%94are%20pulling%20back.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Fisher%20said%2C%20if%20the%20US%20keeps%20borrowing%20more%20money%2C%20a%20glut%20of%20supply%20in%20the%20bond%20market%20will%20eventually%20weigh%20prices%20down%2C%20pushing%20yields%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20would%20create%20a%20difficult%20feedback%20loop%20of%20rising%20debt%20and%20rising%20interest%20payments%2C%20meaning%20the%20government%20has%20to%20spend%20more%20to%20service%20its%20debt.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlready%2C%20the%20US%20is%20on%20track%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%