ons%20are%20sent%20to%20particular%20users%20when%20they%20are%20individually%20targeted%20because%20of%20who%20they%20are%20or%20what%20they%20do%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Findia-news%2Fgovernment-launches-investigation-into-apple-s-snooping-attempt-alert-123103101112_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Findia-news%2Fgovernment-launches-investigation-into-apple-s-snooping-attempt-alert-123103101112_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Findia-news%2Fgovernment-launches-investigation-into-apple-s-snooping-attempt-alert-123103101112_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%26quot%3BElection%20Funding%20A%20Complicated%20Issue%26quot%3B%3A%20Supreme%20Court%20On%20Electoral%20Bonds%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20%26quot%3Bopaque%26quot%3B%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%20for%20funding%20political%20parties%20will%20%26quot%3Bdestroy%20democracy%26quot%3B%20as%20it%20promotes%20corruption%20and%20does%20not%20allow%20a%20level%20playing%20field%20between%20the%20ruling%20and%20opposition%20parties%2C%20the%20petitioners%20challenging%20the%20validity%20of%20the%20scheme%20told%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20which%20on%20Tuesday%20observed%20election%20funding%20was%20a%20%26quot%3Bcomplicated%20issue%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAdvocate%20Prashant%20Bhushan%2C%20appearing%20for%20petitioner%20NGO%20Association%20for%20Democratic%20Reforms%20(ADR)%2C%20told%20a%20five-judge%20constitution%20bench%20headed%20by%20Chief%20Justice%20DY%20Chandrachud%20that%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%20defeats%20the%20citizen's%20right%20to%20be%20informed%20about%20the%20sources%20of%20funding%20of%20political%20parties%20which%20is%20a%20fundamental%20right%20under%20Article%2019(1)(a)%20of%20the%20Constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ECommencing%20the%20arguments%20on%20a%20batch%20of%20pleas%20challenging%20the%20validity%20of%20the%20scheme%2C%20Mr%20Bhushan%20said%20this%20%26quot%3Bopaque%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Banonymous%20instrument%26quot%3B%20promotes%20corruption%20in%20the%20country%20and%20there%20is%20a%20good%20reason%20to%20believe%20that%20these%20bonds%20are%20being%20given%20by%20way%20of%20kickbacks%20to%20parties%20in%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B...that%20it%20(electoral%20bonds)%20disturbs%20and%20indeed%20destroys%20democracy%20in%20this%20country%20because%20it%20does%20not%20allow%20a%20level%20playing%20field%20between%20political%20parties%20which%20are%20ruling%20and%20political%20parties%20which%20are%20in%20opposition%20or%20between%20political%20parties%20and%20independent%20candidates%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20the%20bench%2C%20also%20comprising%20Justices%20Sanjiv%20Khanna%2C%20BR%20Gavai%2C%20JB%20Pardiwala%20and%20Manoj%20Misra.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMr%20Bhushan%20referred%20to%20a%20chart%20and%20said%20as%20per%20the%20party-wise%20donations%20received%20through%20electoral%20bonds%20until%202021-2022%20declared%20in%20the%20audit%20report%2C%20the%20BJP%20received%20Rs%205%2C271%20crore%2C%20while%20the%20Congress%20got%20Rs%20952%20crore.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20gave%20figures%20about%20the%20donations%20received%20by%20other%20political%20parties%20through%20electoral%20bonds%20during%20the%20period%20until%202021-2022%2C%20which%20included%20Rs%20767%20crore%20to%20the%20TMC%2C%20Rs%2063%20crore%20that%20went%20to%20the%20NCP's%20kitty%20and%20Rs%2048%20crore%20to%20the%20Aam%20Aadmi%20Party.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20only%20significant%20contributions%20are%20all%20to%20the%20ruling%20parties%20either%20at%20the%20Centre%20or%20the%20states%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20there%20were%20no%20significant%20contributions%20to%20parties%20which%20are%20not%20in%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20will%20destroy%20democracy.%20Already%20our%20democracy%20was%20almost%20a%20money%20game.%20It%20has%20become%20a%20money%20game%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Bhushan%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EArguing%20that%20money%20power%20or%20unequal%20use%20of%20money%20power%20erodes%20the%20concept%20of%20free%20and%20fair%20elections%2C%20Mr%20Bhushan%20said%20almost%20all%20electoral%20bonds%20have%20been%20received%20only%20by%20parties%20in%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20over%2050%20per%20cent%20of%20all%20such%20donations%20has%20been%20received%20by%20the%20ruling%20party%20at%20the%20Centre%20and%20the%20rest%20have%20gone%20to%20the%20ruling%20parties%20in%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BElection%20funding%20is%20a%20major%20issue.%20It%20is%20not%20something%20very%20simple.%20It%20is%20a%20complicated%20issue%2C%26quot%3B%20Justice%20Khanna%20observed%20during%20the%20day-long%20hearing.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESenior%20advocate%20Kapil%20Sibal%2C%20who%20appeared%20for%20one%20of%20the%20petitioners%2C%20said%20capital%20and%20influence%20go%20hand%20in%20hand%2C%20and%20the%20electoral%20process%20must%20be%20such%20that%20it%20provides%20a%20level%20playing%20field%20to%20all%20participants.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFree%20and%20fair%20election%20is%20the%20basic%20structure%20of%20the%20Constitution%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Sibal%20said%2C%20adding%20the%20moment%20one%20allows%20the%20corporate%20sector%20to%20donate%2C%20whether%20with%20or%20without%20transparency%2C%20it%20is%20inconsistent%20with%20the%20concept%20of%20a%20corporate%20sector%20which%20is%20in%20the%20business%20of%20doing%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20CJI%20observed%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20is%20not%20on%20the%20challenge%20to%20the%20legality%20of%20a%20law%20providing%20for%20corporate%20donations%20per%20se%20as%20that%20wider%20issue%20is%20not%20before%20it%20in%20this%20matter.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMr%20Sibal%20said%20the%20Indian%20Constitution%20is%20%26quot%3Bcitizen-centric%26quot%3B%20and%20every%20scheme%20must%20have%20a%20legitimate%20object%20which%20is%20constitutional%20and%20the%20scheme%20must%20be%20proportionate%20to%20the%20object%20sought%20to%20be%20achieved.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMr%20Sibal%20said%20it%20is%20dangerous%20if%20the%20voice%20of%20people%20is%20drowned%20by%20the%20voice%20of%20the%20corporate%20sector.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAdvocate%20Shadan%20Farasat%2C%20appearing%20for%20the%20Communist%20Party%20of%20India%20(Marxist)%2C%20which%20is%20one%20of%20the%20petitioners%20in%20the%20case%2C%20said%20they%20are%20the%20political%20party%20which%20has%20taken%20a%20conscious%20decision%20not%20to%20accept%20any%20electoral%20bonds.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20architecture%20and%20effect%20of%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%20is%20not%20to%20reduce%20black%20money%20funding%20of%20political%20parties%20but%20to%20re-route%20the%20non-anonymous%20banking%20channel%20funding%20to%20anonymous%20electoral%20bonds%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20the%20%26quot%3Binformational%20black%20hole%26quot%3B%20which%20the%20scheme%20creates%20goes%20against%20the%20concept%20of%20informed%20electorate%20under%20Article%2019(1)(a)%20read%20with%20Article%20326%20of%20the%20Constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EArticle%20326%20of%20the%20Constitution%20deals%20with%20elections%20to%20the%20House%20of%20the%20People%20(Lok%20Sabha)%20and%20to%20the%20legislative%20assemblies%20of%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAdvocate%20Nizam%20Pasha%2C%20who%20appeared%20for%20one%20of%20the%20petitioners%2C%20said%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%20is%20manifestly%20arbitrary.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20asked%20if%20the%20security%20of%20the%20State%20is%20impacted%20if%20a%20foreign%20entity%20invests%20in%20the%20manufacturing%20sector%20in%20India%2C%20is%20it%20not%20impacted%20if%20Chinese%20investment%20is%20coming%20into%20a%20political%20party%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20a%20matter%20of%20policy.%20You%20are%20saying%20that%20a%20company%20in%20China%2C%20since%20China%20shares%20a%20land%20border%2C%20they%20cannot%20bid%20for%20a%20contract%20but%20your%20case%20here%20is%20that%20they%20may%20have%20invested%20in%20electoral%20bonds%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20CJI%20observed.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20hearing%20remained%20inconclusive%20and%20will%20continue%20on%20Wednesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20scheme%2C%20which%20was%20notified%20by%20the%20government%20on%20January%202%2C%202018%2C%20was%20pitched%20as%20an%20alternative%20to%20cash%20donations%20made%20to%20political%20parties%20as%20part%20of%20efforts%20to%20bring%20in%20transparency%20in%20political%20funding.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20provisions%20of%20the%20scheme%2C%20electoral%20bonds%20may%20be%20purchased%20by%20any%20citizen%20of%20India%20or%20entity%20incorporated%20or%20established%20in%20India.%20An%20individual%20can%20buy%20electoral%20bonds%2C%20either%20singly%20or%20jointly%20with%20other%20individuals.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOnly%20the%20political%20parties%20registered%20under%20Section%2029A%20of%20the%20Representation%20of%20the%20People%20Act%2C%201951%20and%20which%20secured%20not%20less%20than%20one%20per%20cent%20of%20the%20votes%20polled%20in%20the%20last%20election%20to%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20or%20a%20state%20legislative%20assembly%20are%20eligible%20to%20receive%20electoral%20bonds.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20notification%2C%20electoral%20bonds%20shall%20be%20encashed%20by%20an%20eligible%20political%20party%20only%20through%20an%20account%20with%20an%20authorised%20bank.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAttorney%20General%20R%20Venkataramani%2C%20in%20a%20statement%20filed%20before%20the%20top%20court%20in%20the%20matter%2C%20has%20said%20citizens%20do%20not%20have%20the%20right%20to%20seek%20information%20under%20Article%2019(1)(a)%20of%20the%20Constitution%20about%20the%20source%20of%20the%20funds.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHolding%20that%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%20for%20funding%20political%20parties%20contributes%20to%20clean%20money%2C%20the%20top%20law%20officer%20has%20said%20there%20can%20be%20no%20general%20right%20to%20know%20%26quot%3Banything%20and%20everything%26quot%3B%2C%20without%20being%20subjected%20to%20reasonable%20restrictions.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20had%2C%20on%20October%2010%2C%20taken%20note%20of%20Mr%20Bhushan's%20submission%20that%20the%20matter%20needed%20adjudication%20before%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%20opens%20for%20the%202024%20general%20election%20to%20the%20Lok%20Sabha.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20January%2020%2C%202020%2C%20the%20court%20had%20refused%20to%20grant%20an%20interim%20stay%20on%20the%20scheme%20and%20sought%20the%20responses%20of%20the%20Centre%20and%20the%20Election%20Commission%20to%20an%20interim%20application%20filed%20by%20the%20NGO%20seeking%20a%20stay%20on%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20had%2C%20in%20April%202019%2C%20also%20declined%20to%20stay%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%20and%20said%20it%20will%20accord%20an%20in-depth%20hearing%20on%20the%20pleas%20as%20the%20Centre%20and%20the%20EC%20had%20raised%20%26quot%3Bweighty%20issues%26quot%3B%20that%20had%20%26quot%3Btremendous%20bearing%20on%20the%20sanctity%20of%20the%20electoral%20process%20in%20the%20country%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698773820000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-10%2Fe8bgk2vo_supreme-court-getty_625x300_31_October_23.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Felection-funding-a-complicated-issue-supreme-court-on-electoral-bonds-4533148%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20%26quot%3Bopaque%26quot%3B%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%20will%20%26quot%3Bdestroy%20democracy%26quot%3B%20as%20it%20does%20not%20allow%20a%20level%20playing%20field%20between%20the%20ruling%20and%20