%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Fglobalsarang%2Fstatus%2F1718339406753362159%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eanomaly%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20was%20the%20cluster%20of%20Pacific%20Island%20states%2C%20although%20they%20tend%20to%20vote%20with%20the%20US%20on%20many%20international%20issues.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20the%20Philippines%2C%20aligned%20with%20the%20West%2C%20abstained%20because%20it%20said%20it%20recognised%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Cright%20to%20self-defence%E2%80%9D%2C%20what%20raised%20eyebrows%20across%20the%20Global%20South%20was%20India%E2%80%99s%20refusal%20to%20back%20the%20UNGA%20call%20for%20a%20humanitarian%20pause.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%20claimed%20that%20it%20didn%E2%80%99t%20vote%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20UNGA%20resolution%20because%20the%20text%20didn%E2%80%99t%20explicitly%20criticise%20the%20October%207%20terror%20attack%20by%20Hamas.%20Incidentally%2C%20India%20has%20not%20mentioned%20Hamas%20in%20any%20of%20its%20public%20statements%2C%20including%20its%20Explanation%20of%20Vote.%20As%20an%20aside%2C%20the%20last%20time%20that%20Hamas%20was%20mentioned%20by%20India%20was%20in%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mea.gov.in%2Fmedia-briefings.htm%3Fdtl%2F3466%2Fstatement%2Bby%2Bofficial%2Bspokesman%2Bon%2Bthe%2Bkilling%2Bof%2Bhamas%2Bleader%2Babdel%2Baziz%2Brantisi%5C%22%20data-stringify-link%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mea.gov.in%2Fmedia-briefings.htm%3Fdtl%2F3466%2Fstatement%2Bby%2Bofficial%2Bspokesman%2Bon%2Bthe%2Bkilling%2Bof%2Bhamas%2Bleader%2Babdel%2Baziz%2Brantisi%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%20data-sk%3D%5C%22tooltip_parent%5C%22%3EApril%202004%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20when%20the%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%20said%20that%20the%20targeted%20assassination%20of%20Hamas%20leader%20Abdel%20Aziz%20Rantisi%20was%20%E2%80%9Cunjustified%20and%20unacceptable%20and%20cannot%20be%20condoned%20under%20any%20circumstances%E2%80%9D.%20%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%2C%20as%20now%2C%20the%20party%20in%20power%20in%20India%20was%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party.%20%3Cspan%3ERantisi%20was%20killed%20by%20the%20Israeli%20Air%20Force.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELast%20week%20at%20the%20UN%2C%20India%20was%20the%20only%20South%20Asian%20country%20to%20not%20vote%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20resolution.%20Similarly%2C%20the%20Philippines%20was%20the%20only%20Southeast%20Asian%20country%20to%20not%20vote%20positively%2C%20with%20Cambodia%20not%20recording%20its%20vote.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20to%20Shidore%2C%20the%20global%20south%20strongly%20wants%20the%20war%20to%20end%20and%20has%20been%20critical%20of%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20actions.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Fglobalsarang%2Fstatus%2F1718339408053596169%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20estimates%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20in%20the%20Global%20South%2C%20outside%20West%20Asia%2C%20more%20than%2070%25%20of%20countries%20voted%20in%20favour%20of%20Jordan%E2%80%99s%20resolution%2C%20while%20around%2023%25%20abstained%20and%20only%20around%207%25%20voted%20against.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBreaking%20it%20down%20geographically%2C%20he%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Fglobalsarang%2Fstatus%2F1718339405323137431%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Enoted%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%2030%20African%20countries%2C%2026%20Latin%20American%20countries%2C%20nine%20Southeast%20Asian%20countries%20and%20five%20South%20Asian%20countries%20had%20voted%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20resolution.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20following%20is%20an%20edited%20version%20of%20the%20interview%20conducted%20via%20e-mail.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIs%20it%20correct%20to%20say%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20aftermath%20of%20this%20UNGA%20resolution%2C%20that%20there%20is%20even%20greater%20divergence%20from%20the%20West%20and%20a%20more%20unified%20consensus%20in%20the%20Global%20South%20in%20the%20latest%20eruption%20of%20the%20Israel-Palestine%20dispute%20compared%20to%20the%20Ukraine%20war%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EYes%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%20(West%20Asia)%20among%20its%C2%A0citizenry.%20Middle%20Eastern%20governments%20however%20remain%20more%20ambivalent%2C%20but%20they%20are%20being%20forced%20into%20a%20more%20critical%20stance%20toward%20Israel%20and%20the%20US%20due%20to%20public%20pressure.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20is%20your%20analysis%20of%20the%20voting%20record%20of%20the%20Global%20South%20to%20the%20October%2027%20UNGA%20resolution%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20analysis%20is%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Fglobalsarang%2Fstatus%2F1718339398205424004%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Emy%20Twitter%20thread%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20The%20noteworthy%20additional%20element%20is%20that%20several%20Global%20South%20states%20%E2%80%93%20largely%20in%20Latin%20America%2C%20though%20also%20key%20African%20ones%20such%20as%20Kenya%20and%20Nigeria%20%E2%80%93%20preferred%20to%20add%20language%20proposed%20by%20the%20US%20and%20Canada%20condemning%20Hamas%20and%20mentioning%20Israeli%20hostages%2C%20but%20this%20preference%20was%20not%20a%20barrier%20in%20their%20clear%20support%20for%20the%20adopted%20resolution%20calling%20for%20a%20%E2%80%9Chumanitarian%20truce%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20factors%20have%20driven%20such%20a%20robust%20response%20from%20Global%20South%20members%3F%20Is%20it%20rooted%20in%20a%20perception%20of%20Western%20hypocrisy%2C%20considerations%20of%20domestic%20public%20opinion%2C%20or%20national%20interests%20and%20external%20influences%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPublic%20opinion%20is%20a%20strong%20factor%C2%A0in%20the%20Middle%20East.%20The%20view%20that%20the%20US%20practices%20double%20standards%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20conflict%20and%20human%20rights%20is%20by%20now%20well-known%20across%20the%20non-Western%20world%20and%20understood%2C%20but%20the%20Gaza%20crisis%20will%20only%20further%20entrench%20this%20perception.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIs%20it%20reasonable%20to%20anticipate%20that%20the%20growing%20prominence%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98Global%20South%E2%80%99%20in%20discussions%20will%20bring%20about%20a%20shift%20in%20policies%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIf%20this%20war%20lasts%20much%20longer%20or%20escalates%2C%20the%20governments%20may%20take%20further%20steps%20and%20there%20could%20be%20a%20major%20realignment%20away%20from%20the%20US%20%E2%80%93%20but%20we%20are%20not%20there%20yet.%20In%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20Global%20South%2C%20this%20is%20one%20of%20many%20factors%20that%20is%20increasing%20alienation%20from%20the%20West%2C%20though%20it%20is%20still%20incremental.%20The%20other%20important%20point%20here%20is%20that%20not%20all%20Global%20South%20states%20are%20following%20this%20trend.%20India%20and%20the%20Philippines%20are%20two%20major%20exceptions%20%E2%80%93%20both%20have%20been%20relatively%20sympathetic%20to%20Israeli%20and%20US%20positions%20on%20the%20matter.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20400px)%2085vw%2C%20400px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F31202656%2FL1UHcYgb_400x400.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22400%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F31202656%2FL1UHcYgb_400x400.jpg%20400w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F31202656%2FL1UHcYgb_400x400-300x300.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F31202656%2FL1UHcYgb_400x400-150x150.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-682813%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22400%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESarang%20Shidore%20Photo%3A%20X%2F%40globalsarang%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHas%20the%20current%20world%20order%20evolved%20enough%20to%20empower%20the%20Global%20South%20to%20play%20a%20more%20substantive%20role%20compared%20to%20the%20Non-Aligned%20Movement%20during%20the%20Cold%20War%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMiddle%20Eastern%20states%2C%20if%20they%20took%20a%20much%20tougher%20stance%20toward%20the%20US%20and%20Israel%2C%20could%20have%20some%20impact%20on%20the%20war.%20The%20rest%20of%20the%20Global%20South%20will%20have%20less%20impact.%20However%2C%20these%20developments%20will%20not%20heal%20but%20only%20deepen%20the%20divergence%20between%20the%20West%20and%20most%20of%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20Global%20South.%20It%20is%20one%20factor%20of%20several.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIs%20a%20unified%20stance%20from%20the%20Global%20South%20a%20prerequisite%20for%20Western%20nations%20to%20take%20heed%3F%20Alternatively%2C%20is%20it%20more%20plausible%20that%20the%20rapid%20rise%20of%20specific%20nations%20within%20the%20Global%20South%2C%20bolstered%20by%20their%20economic%20clout%2C%20will%20prompt%20them%20to%20adapt%20their%20policies%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20my%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.foreignaffairs.com%2Fworld%2Freturn-global-south-critique-western-power%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EForeign%20Affairs%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20article%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20I%20noted%20that%20the%20biggest%20way%20that%20the%20Global%20South%20is%20asserting%20itself%20is%20through%20the%20actions%20of%20individual%20states.%20As%20I%20wrote%2C%20%E2%80%9CThese%20diverse%20and%20mostly%20uncoordinated%20actions%2C%20grounded%20strongly%20in%20the%20national%20interest%20of%20each%20country%2C%20are%20likely%20to%20have%20an%20impact%20greater%20than%20the%20sum%20of%20their%20parts.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMany%20Global%20South%20states%20are%20wealthier%20and%20savvier%20than%20they%20were%20in%20the%2020th%20century%20and%20have%20learned%20how%20to%20play%20off%20both%20sides%20to%20gain%20benefits%20for%20themselves.%20Compared%20to%20the%20Cold%20War%20period%2C%20their%20guiding%20principle%20is%20not%20%E2%80%9Cidealism%2C%20but%20realism%2C%20with%20an%20unhesitating%20embrace%20of%20national%20interests%20and%20increased%20recourse%20to%20power%20politics%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698768943000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F31202909%2Fisrael-palestine.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Findia-global-south-gaza-israel-sarang-shidore-interview%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22'The%20view%20that%20the%20US%20practices%20double%20standards%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20conflict%20and%20human%20rights%20is%20by%20now%20well-known%20across%20the%20non-Western%20world%20and%20understood%2C%20but%20the%20Gaza%20crisis%20will%20only%20further%20entrench%20this%20perception%2C'%20says%20Sarang%20Shidore%20of%20the%20Quincy%20Institute.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Findia-global-south-gaza-israel-sarang-shidore-interview%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Gaza%20Has%20Become%20A%20%26quot%3BGraveyard%26quot%3B%20For%20Thousands%20Of%20Children%3A%20UN%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20Gaza%20Strip%20has%20become%20a%20graveyard%20for%20thousands%20of%20children%2C%20the%20United%20Nations%20said%20Tuesday%2C%20as%20it%20feared%20the%20prospect%20of%20more%20dying%20of%20dehydration.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIsrael%20has%20heavily%20bombarded%20Gaza%20since%20Hamas%20gunmen%20stormed%20across%20the%20border%20on%20October%207%2C%20killing%201%2C400%20people%2C%20mostly%20civilians%2C%20and%20kidnapping%20at%20least%20240%20others%2C%20according%20to%20Israeli%20officials.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20health%20ministry%20in%20the%20Hamas-run%20Gaza%20Strip%20said%20the%20strikes%20have%20killed%20more%20than%208%2C500%20people%2C%20mainly%20civilians.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20UN%20children's%20agency%20UNICEF%20said%20there%20was%20a%20risk%20that%20the%20number%20of%20child%20deaths%20directly%20from%20bombardment%20could%20become%20eclipsed.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20gravest%20fears%20about%20the%20reported%20numbers%20of%20children%20killed%20becoming%20dozens%2C%20then%20hundreds%2C%20and%20ultimately%20thousands%20were%20realised%20in%20just%20a%20fortnight%2C%26quot%3B%20UNICEF%20spokesman%20James%20Elder%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20numbers%20are%20appalling%3B%20reportedly%20more%20than%203%2C450%20children%20killed%3B%20staggeringly%20this%20rises%20significantly%20every%20day.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGaza%20has%20become%20a%20graveyard%20for%20thousands%20of%20children.%20It's%20a%20living%20hell%20for%20everyone%20else.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20the%20more%20than%20one%20million%20children%20living%20in%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%20were%20also%20suffering%20from%20a%20lack%20of%20clean%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGaza's%20water%20production%20capacity%20is%20a%20mere%20five%20percent%20of%20its%20usual%20daily%20output.%20Child%20deaths%20--%20particularly%20infants%20--%20to%20dehydration%20are%20a%20growing%20threat%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EUNICEF%20is%20calling%20for%20an%20immediate%20humanitarian%20ceasefire%2C%20with%20all%20access%20crossings%20into%20Gaza%20opened%20for%20the%20safe%2C%20sustained%20and%20unimpeded%20access%20of%20humanitarian%20aid%2C%20including%20water%2C%20food%2C%20medical%20supplies%2C%20and%20fuel.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnd%20if%20there%20is%20no%20ceasefire%2C%20no%20water%2C%20no%20medicine%2C%20and%20no%20release%20of%20abducted%20children%3F%20Then%20we%20hurtle%20towards%20even%20greater%20horrors%20afflicting%20innocent%20children%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Elder.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20certainly%20children%20who%20are%20dying%20who%20have%20been%20impacted%20by%20the%20bombardment%20but%20should%20have%20had%20their%20lives%20saved%2C%26quot%3B%20Elder%20told%20reporters%20in%20Geneva%2C%20via%20video-link.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20without%20greater%20humanitarian%20access%20into%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%2C%20%26quot%3Bthen%20the%20deaths%20from%20the%20attacks%2C%20they%20could%20absolutely%20be%20the%20tip%20of%20the%20iceberg%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EElder%20said%20that%20according%20to%20figures%20from%20health%20faculties%20in%20the%20Hamas-run%20Gaza%20Strip%2C%20some%20940%20children%20were%20missing.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EUN%20humanitarian%20agency%20spokesman%20Jens%20Laerke%20added%3A%20%26quot%3BIt's%20almost%20unbearable%20to%20think%20about%20children%20buried%20under%20rubble%2C%20but%20(with)%20very%20little%20opportunity%20or%20possibility%20for%20getting%20them%20out.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20World%20Health%20Organization%20said%20people%20in%20Gaza%20were%20dying%20not%20just%20from%20direct%20bombardment.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20130%20premature%20infants%20that%20are%20dependent%20on%20incubators%2C%20of%20which%2061%20percent%20approximately%20are%20in%20the%20north%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20WHO%20spokesman%20Christian%20Lindmeier.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20an%20imminent%20public%20health%20catastrophe%20that%20looms%20with%20the%20mass%20displacement%2C%20the%20overcrowding%2C%20and%20the%20damage%20to%20water%20and%20sanitation%20infrastructure.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3