20Weaponising%20Terror%20Financing%2C%20Money%20Laundering%20Laws%20Against%20NGOs%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F06%2F21145151%2FScreen-Shot-2019-06-21-at-2.51.45-PM.v1.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMumbai%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Ahead%20of%20the%20Mutual%20Evaluation%20Review%20(MER)%20scheduled%20on%20November%203%20to%20evaluate%20the%20anti-money%20laundering%20laws%20and%20financing%20of%20terrorism%20in%20India%2C%20a%20shadow%20report%20compiled%20by%20anonymous%20civil%20society%20actors%20and%20forwarded%20to%20the%20FATF%20by%20the%20Global%20NPO%20Coalition%20on%20FATF%20shows%20that%20India%20has%20weaponised%20its%20laws%20to%20target%20and%20stifle%20non-profit%20organisations%20(NPOs)%20in%20the%20country.%20The%20MER%20is%20an%20assessment%20of%20a%20country%E2%80%99s%20measures%20to%20combat%20money%20laundering%20and%20the%20financing%20of%20terrorism%20and%20proliferation%20of%20weapons%20of%20mass%20destruction.%20The%20MER%20would%20be%20followed%20by%20a%20plenary%20discussion%20in%20June%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20shadow%20report%2C%20based%20on%20interviewing%20representatives%20of%20over%20700%20NGOs%20and%20field%20experts%2C%20finds%20that%20the%20Indian%20government%20%E2%80%93%20without%20involving%20or%20informing%20the%20NGOs%20about%20the%20ways%20of%20the%20Financial%20Action%20Task%20Force%20(FATF)%20%E2%80%93%20has%20been%20indiscriminately%20targeting%20them%20on%20%E2%80%9Cunproven%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cfrivolous%20claims%E2%80%9D.%20The%20FATF%2C%20an%20intergovernmental%20organisation%20established%20in%201989%20by%20the%20Group%20of%20Seven%20(G-7)%20countries%2C%20leads%20a%20global%20action%20to%20tackle%20money%20laundering%2C%20terrorist%20and%20proliferation%20financing.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%2046-page%20shadow%20report%20identifies%20multiple%20counts%20on%20which%20India%20is%20non-compliant%20with%20FATF%20standards%20and%20has%20failed%20to%20act%20upon%20the%20recommendations%20made%20by%20the%20intergovernmental%20organisation%20in%20the%202010%20MER%20of%20India.%20In%202010%2C%20the%20MER%20specifically%20noted%20that%20India%20had%20no%20comprehensive%20assessment%20of%20its%20financial%20institutions.%20In%20addition%2C%20the%20MER%20had%20also%20recommended%20India%20undertake%20a%20detailed%20risk%20assessment%20of%20the%20NPO%20sector%20for%20terrorist%20financing.%20Even%2013%20years%20after%20the%20recommendation%2C%20according%20to%20the%20study%2C%20India%20has%20not%20made%20public%20whether%20or%20not%20it%20has%20carried%20out%20any%20work%20to%20identify%20such%20risks%20in%20the%20NPO%20sector.%20Instead%2C%20the%20report%20says%3A%20%E2%80%9CIt%20follows%20a%20one-size-fits-all%20approach%20that%20targets%20the%20entire%20NPO%20sector%20based%20on%20unproven%20or%20frivolous%20claims.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIndia%2C%20in%20the%20MER%202010%2C%20by%20its%20own%20admission%2C%20had%20said%20that%20the%20risk%20of%20terrorist%20financing%20among%20NPOs%20in%20India%20is%20small.%20However%2C%20in%20the%20past%20decade%2C%20more%20specifically%20after%20the%20Narendra%20Modi-led%20BJP%20government%20came%20to%20power%2C%20the%20number%20of%20refused%20licenses%20to%20the%20NGOs%20has%20rocketed%20from%2041%20in%202010%20to%2020%2C693%20NGOs%20in%202023.%20This%20represents%20an%20increase%20of%20refusals%20by%2050%2C000%25.%20The%20refusal%20of%20licenses%20became%20possible%20after%20the%20scope%20(to%20control%20and%20prosecute)%20of%20The%20Foreign%20Contribution%20(Regulation)%20Act%2C%202010%20expanded%20exponentially.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAlthough%20set%20up%20in%201989%2C%20the%20FATF%20went%20through%20a%20significant%20change%20post-September%2011%2C%202001%20twin%20blast%20in%20the%20US.%20The%20FATF%20revised%20its%20recommendations%2C%20and%20nine%20special%20recommendations%20were%20added%20to%20the%20initial%2040.%20One%20of%20them%20specifically%20dealt%20with%20the%20NPOs%20that%20were%20%E2%80%9Cparticularly%20vulnerable%20to%20terrorist%20financing%20abuse%E2%80%9D.%20In%202008%2C%20FATF%20published%20a%20typology%20report%20focusing%20on%20the%20funding%20pattern%20of%20terrorist%20organisations%20and%20noted%20that%20%E2%80%9Ccharities%20are%20attractive%20to%20terrorist%20networks%20as%20a%20means%20to%20move%20funds%E2%80%9D.%20This%20very%20generic%20observation%20attracted%20flak%20from%20all%20quarters%20and%20it%20was%20noted%20that%20this%20specific%20recommendation%20without%20a%20clear%20rationale%20was%20%E2%80%9Ca%20danger%20to%20civil%20society%20organisations%20because%20it%20enabled%20governments%20to%20bring%20in%20repressive%20laws%20under%20the%20garb%20of%20regulating%20NPOs%E2%80%9D.%20And%20the%20fear%20came%20true%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20primary%20legislation%20regulating%20cross-border%20funding%20for%20NPOs%20in%20India%20is%20the%20Foreign%20Contribution%20(Regulation)%20Act%2C%202010.%20When%20it%20was%20passed%2C%20the%20primary%20concern%20highlighted%20that%20over%20half%20of%20the%20NPOs%20did%20not%20declare%20their%20foreign%20contributions.%20When%20the%20FCRA%20law%20was%20first%20enacted%20in%201967%2C%20the%20main%20focus%20of%20the%20Act%20remained%20on%20the%20prohibition%20of%20foreign%20funds%20in%20domestic%20elections.%20But%20ironically%2C%20in%202018%2C%20political%20parties%20were%20made%20explicitly%20exempt%20from%20scrutiny%20of%20funds%20they%20received%20from%20abroad%20through%20the%20passage%20of%20the%20Finance%20Bill%202018%2C%20which%20was%20passed%20without%20debate.%20This%20shift%2C%20the%20shadow%20report%20says%2C%20denotes%20how%20the%20Indian%20government%20perceives%20NPOs.%20While%20former%20Prime%20Minister%20Manmohan%20Singh%20accused%20NPOs%20of%20blocking%20the%20building%20of%20a%20nuclear%20power%20plant%20in%20India%2C%20Modi%20has%20gone%20several%20steps%20ahead%20and%20accused%20NPOs%20of%20conspiring%20to%20remove%20him%20from%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%202020%2C%20the%20FCRA%20law%20was%20made%20more%20stringent%20by%20prohibiting%20organisations%20from%20sub-granting%20to%20other%20organisations%2C%20and%20this%20amendment%20came%20into%20force%20amidst%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%2C%20in%20which%20over%205.32%20lakh%20deaths%20were%20reported%20in%20the%20country.%20The%20researchers%20of%20the%20shadow%20report%2C%20through%20conversations%20with%20a%20range%20of%20international%20funders%2C%20as%20well%20as%20organisations%20working%20on%20the%20ground%20in%20India%20to%20address%20the%20COVID-19%20crisis%2C%20have%20established%20a%20consistent%20pattern%20of%20misuse%20of%20FATF-inspired%20laws%20in%20the%20regulation%20of%20nonprofits%20leading%20to%20critical%20supplies%20being%20denied%20to%20NPOs%20at%20a%20time%20when%20human%20lives%20were%20at%20stake.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20officials%20from%20an%20international%20donor%20organisation%20states%3A%20%E2%80%9CDespite%20timely%20intervention%20by%20international%20donor%20agencies%20to%20provide%20resources%2C%20India%20represented%20unique%20challenges%20when%20it%20came%20to%20receiving%20funds.%20Unfortunately%2C%20the%20challenges%20were%20artificially%20created%20by%20the%20government%20despite%20a%20severe%20need%20for%20relief%20work.%E2%80%9D%20Contrary%20to%20the%20logistical%20challenges%20faced%20in%20other%20countries%2C%20in%20India%2C%20the%20primary%20hurdle%20for%20getting%20funds%20to%20those%20in%20need%20was%20the%20Indian%20government%E2%80%99s%20misuse%20of%20banking%20institutions.%20%E2%80%9CIndia%E2%80%99s%20banking%20institutions%20did%20not%20release%20the%20money%20to%20the%20beneficiary%20organisations%20citing%20security%20concerns%20flagged%20by%20the%20government%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20identifies.%20These%20hurdles%20were%20faced%20by%20many%20domestic%20NGOs%20in%20spite%20of%20recipients%20having%20full%20regulatory%20clearance%2C%20including%20FCRA%20certification.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20report%2C%20basing%20its%20findings%20on%20news%20articles%20and%20individual%20interviews%2C%20points%20out%20that%20central%20agencies%20like%20the%20Enforcement%20Directorate%2C%20the%20Central%20Bureau%20of%20Investigation%20and%20the%20National%20Investigating%20Agency%20have%20become%20%E2%80%9Ca%20political%20tool%20and%20is%20being%20misused%20to%20target%20opposition%20leaders%20and%20civil%20society%20in%20India%E2%80%9D.%20Among%20the%20alarming%20statistics%20is%20the%20number%20of%20cases%20registered%20by%20these%20agencies%20and%20the%20eventual%20success%20(or%20lack%20of)%20in%20proceeding%20with%20them%20in%20the%20courts.%20For%20instance%2C%20of%20the%20over%206%2C000%20cases%20registered%20with%20the%20ED%2C%20only%2025%20have%20gone%20to%20trial.%20The%20number%20of%20cases%20handled%20by%20the%20ED%20has%20dramatically%20increased%20after%20the%202010%20MER%2C%20as%20India%20tripled%20its%20resources%20to%20empower%20the%20central%20agency.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Prevention%20of%20Money%20Laundering%20Act%2C%20under%20which%20the%20ED%20registers%20and%20investigates%20cases%2C%20underwent%20an%20amendment%20in%202012.%20Following%20this%20amendment%2C%20the%20ED%20could%20make%20use%20of%20a%20specific%20section%203%20of%20the%20Act%2C%20which%20covers%20%E2%80%9Call%20activities%20relating%20to%20concealment%2C%20possession%2C%20acquisition%2C%20or%20use%20of%20the%20proceeds%20of%20crime%20and%20projecting%20or%20claiming%20it%20as%20untainted%20property%2C%20within%20the%20offense%20of%20money%20laundering.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20says%3A%20%E2%80%9CA%20perfect%20example%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9Cunintended%20consequences%20of%20FATF%20recommendations%E2%80%9D%20is%20the%20weaponisation%20of%20the%20ED%20in%20India%2C%20which%20is%20being%20used%20as%20a%20political%20tool%20by%20the%20government%20to%20target%20opposition%20leaders%20and%20NPOs%20who%20are%20critical%20of%20the%20government.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20ED%20has%20actively%20gone%20after%20prominent%20international%20NPOs%20like%20Amnesty%20International%2C%20religious%20institutions%20and%20churches%2C%20and%20prominent%20human%20rights%20defenders%2C%20the%20report%20states%20that%20it%20has%20avoided%20investigating%20corporate%20fraud%20and%20serious%20allegations%20of%20stock%20price%20manipulation%20by%20corporations%20close%20to%20the%20ruling%20party%20such%20as%20the%20Adani%20Group.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESimilar%20to%20the%20FCRA%20and%20PMLA%20laws%2C%20the%20government%20also%20brought%20significant%20changes%20to%20the%20Unlawful%20Activities%20(Prevention)%20Act%20in%202012.%20This%20too%20was%20done%20following%20the%202010%20MER.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ELike%20the%20NGOs%20working%20on%20the%20ground%20during%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%2C%20several%20child%20rights%2C%20human%20rights%20and%20environmental%20organisations%20also%20faced%20severe%20pushback%20from%20the%20government.%20Many%20of%20them%2C%20including%20Amnesty%20International%2C%20were%20driven%20out%20of%20India%20in%20the%20past%20years%20after%20cases%20were%20registered%20against%20them%20and%20their%20bank%20accounts%20were%20frozen.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20interviews%20with%2011%20sectoral%20experts%2C%20including%20the%20leadership%20and%20management%20of%20leading%20child%20rights%20organisations%20across%20multiple%20states%2C%20funders%20and%20serving%20and%20former%20bureaucrats%20involved%20in%20the%20regulation%20of%20this%20sector%2C%20the%20report%20found%20that%20most%20of%20them%20%E2%80%9Cexpressed%20significant%20fears%20of%20reprisal%20and%20therefore%20demanded%20anonymity%20as%20a%20condition%20for%20participating%20in%20this%20study%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EStarting%20with%20NGOs%20involved%20in%20organising%20protests%20against%20the%20then-proposed%20Koodankulam%20nuclear%20plant%20as%20early%20as%202011%20to%20Greenpeace%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20many%20NGOs%20have%20been%20forced%20to%20shut%20operations%20in%20the%20country%20under%20the%20accusation%20that%20%E2%80%9Cforeign%20hands%E2%80%9D%20were%20involved%20in%20funding%20environmental%20protests%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20their%20collective%20demand%20before%20the%20FATF%2C%20the%20shadow%20report%20calls%20upon%20India%20to%20%E2%80%9Cstop%20misusing%20FATF%20standards%20to%20target%20legitimate%20NPOs%E2%80%9D.%20The%20report%20has%20also%20recommended%20that%20India%20be%20directed%20to%20revise%20restrictive%20provisions%20of%20the%20FCRA%2C%20PMLA%20and%20UAPA%20that%20violate%20the%20mandate%20of%20recommendations.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Global%20NPO%20Coalition%20and%20Amnesty%20International%20have%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffatfplatform.org%2Fassets%2FLetter-to-FATF_India_final-.pdf%5C%22%3Eraised%20their%20concerns%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20a%20letter%20sent%20to%20FATF%20president%20T.%20Raja%20Kumar.%20They%20have%20asked%20the%20FATF%20to%20%E2%80%9CInclude%20at%20least%20one%20independent%20and%20impartial%20civil%20society%20expert%20either%20directly%20in%20the%20team%20of%20evaluators%20or%20involve%20them%20otherwise%20in%20the%20MER%20process.%20Such%20a%20person%20will%20be%20able%20to%20advise%20the%20team%20on%20the%20nature%20of%20civil%20society%20concerns%20without%20prejudice%20and%20warn%20evaluators%20of%20attempts%20to%20obfuscate%20the%20situation%20on%20the%20ground.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20believe%20that%20the%20upcoming%20evaluation%20presents%20an%20opportunity%20for%20the%20FATF%20to%20denounce%20any%20disproportionate%2C%20arbitrary%2C%20and%20unnecessary%20restrictions%20on%20India%E2%80%99s%20NPO%20sector.%20The%20FATF%20must%20call%20on%20India%20to%20respect%20human%20rights%20and%20their%20international%20obligations.%20By%20including%20an%20independent%20NPO%20expert%20in%20the%20evaluation%20team%20and%20ensuring%20evaluators%20meet%20the%20impacted%20NPOs%2C%20the%20FATF%20can%20ensure%20its%20recommendations%20are%20being%20complied%20with%20by%20the%20Indian%20government%20both%20in%20letter%20and%20in%20spirit%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20letter%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Global%20NPO%20Coalition%20on%20FATF%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffatfplatform.org%2Fabout-us%2F%5C%22%3Ecalls%20itself%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20%E2%80%9Cloose%20network%20of%20diverse%20nonprofit%20organisations%E2%80%9D.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Coalition%20advocates%20for%20improvement%20in%20the%20quality%20and%20effectiveness%20of%20FATF%20Mutual%20Evaluations%20with%20sustained%20outreach%20to%20the%20NPO%20sector%E2%80%A6%20The%20aim%20is%20to%20mitigate%20the%20unintended%20consequences%20of%20countering%20the%20financing%20of%20terrorism%20policies%20on%20civil%20society%20in%20order%20that%20legitimate%20charitable%20activity%20is%20not%20disrupted%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20coalition%20says%20on%20its%20website.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698755420000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F06%2F21145151%2FScreen-Shot-2019-06-21-at-2.51.45-PM.v1.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fahead-of-fatf-meeting-report-says-india-weaponising-terror-financing-money-laundering-laws-against-ngos%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20shadow%20report%20by%20the%20Global%20NPO%20Coalition%20on%20FATF%20finds%20that%20India%20has%20been%20indiscriminately%20targeting%20NGOs%20using%20%E2%80%9Cunproven%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cfrivolous%20claims%E2%80%9D.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A7%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fahead-of-fatf-meeting-report-says-india-weaponising-terror-financing-money-laundering-laws-against-ngos%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Varun%20Tej%20and%20Lavanya%20Tripathi%20Wedding%20LIVE%20Updates%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698755400000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-104857714%