opy-of-Copy-of-Lead-image-size-2.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20recent%20death%20in%20central%20India%20of%20Anne%20Wright%2C%20age%2094%2C%20marks%20the%20end%20of%20an%20era.%20This%20wildlife%20campaigner%2C%20tiger%20enthusiast%2C%20horse%20breeder%2C%20party%20lover%2C%20and%20friend%20of%20leading%20politicians%20and%20royalty%2C%20was%20one%20of%20the%20last%20of%20the%20British%20expatriates%20who%20stayed%20on%20after%20independence%20in%201947.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAnne%20Wright%20died%20on%20October%204%20after%20a%20long%20illness%20at%20her%20family%E2%80%99s%20Kipling%20Camp%20jungle%20resort%20on%20the%20edge%20of%20Kanha%20National%20Park%20in%20Madhya%20Pradesh.%20She%20was%20cremated%2C%20as%20she%20would%20have%20wished%2C%20in%20the%20jungle%20later%20that%20day%20under%20the%20stars.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%201929%2C%20she%20was%20taken%20when%20she%20was%20just%20a%20few%20months%20old%20to%20the%20wilds%20of%20central%20India%20where%20her%20father%2C%20Austen%20Havelock%20Layard%2C%20who%20was%20in%20the%20Indian%20Civil%20Service%2C%20was%20posted.%20She%20spent%20the%20rest%20of%20her%20life%20in%20the%20country%2C%20apart%20from%20schooling%20in%20the%20UK%2C%C2%A0and%20took%20Indian%20nationality%20in%201991.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20her%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thenationalnews.com%2Farts%2Fthe-end-of-empire-1.488200%5C%22%3Eearly%20memories%20was%C2%A0%3C%2Fa%3Estanding%2C%20when%20she%20was%20five%2C%20with%20her%20younger%20sister%20and%20governess%20on%20the%20Kings%20Way%20(later%20Rajpath%20and%20now%20Kartavya%20Path)%20in%20New%20Delhi.%20Wearing%20large%20white%C2%A0%3Cem%3Etopis%3C%2Fem%3E%20(sun%20hats)%2C%20they%20were%20watching%20her%20father%2C%20by%20then%20the%20city%E2%80%99s%20deputy%20commissioner%2C%20process%20past%20with%20the%20Viceroy%20Lord%20Willingdon%20in%201934.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F31160943%2FScreenshot-2023-10-31-at-4.03.08-PM-1.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22873%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F31160943%2FScreenshot-2023-10-31-at-4.03.08-PM-1.jpg%20873w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F31160943%2FScreenshot-2023-10-31-at-4.03.08-PM-1-300x213.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-682725%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22620%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EAnne%20Wright.%20Photo%3A%20sanctuarynaturefoundation.org%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EAt%20Mahatma%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20cremation%20in%20Delhi%20in%20January%201948%2C%20she%20sat%20with%20members%20of%20the%20family%20of%C2%A0Lord%20Louis%20Mountbatten%2C%20the%20last%20British%20governor%20general.%C2%A0She%20remembered%20being%20terrified%20by%20the%20vast%20sea%20of%20people.%C2%A0While%20visiting%20her%20friend%20Rita%20Pandit%2C%20prime%20minister%20Jawaharal%20Nehru%E2%80%99s%20niece%20at%20his%20Teen%20Murti%20residence%20in%20Delhi%2C%20they%20went%20into%20his%20bedroom%20where%20she%20saw%20a%20photo%20of%20Edwina%2C%20Mountbatten%E2%80%99s%20wife%2C%20on%20the%20bedside%20table%20%E2%80%93%20poignant%20evidence%20of%20the%20Edwina-Nehru%20relationship.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20a%20grand%20life.%20She%20told%20John%20Zubrzycki%20for%20a%20book%20he%20was%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.co.uk%2FHouse-Jaipur-Inside-Glamorous-Family%2Fdp%2F9353451175%5C%22%3Ewriting%20on%20the%20Jaipur%3C%2Fa%3E%20dynasty%2C%20how%20as%20a%20young%20bride%20in%20the%201950s%20she%20had%20gone%20as%20a%20guest%20of%20the%20royal%20family%20to%20the%20princely%20state%20of%20Cooch%20Behar%20in%20what%20is%20now%20West%20Bengal.%20At%20the%20age%20of%2090%20she%20could%20%E2%80%9Cstill%20vividly%20recall%20landing%20on%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20grass%20airstrip%20in%20the%20dilapidated%20DC3%20being%20operated%20by%20Jamair%E2%80%9D.%20On%20arrival%2C%20%E2%80%9Cguests%20would%20be%20met%20by%20elephants%20that%20would%20transport%20them%20and%20their%20luggage%20to%20the%20palace.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20small%2C%20slight%20and%20elegant%20lady%20with%20a%20winning%20smile%20and%20sparkling%20eyes%2C%20she%20could%20be%20tough%20and%20determined.%20She%20showed%20this%20in%20an%20extraordinary%20exchange%20of%20letters%20asking%20Indira%20Gandhi%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20prime%20minister%2C%20to%20lobby%20Pakistan%E2%80%99s%20and%20Afghanistan%E2%80%99s%20leaders%20at%20a%20Commonwealth%20summit%20meeting%20in%201983%20about%20the%20plight%20of%20the%20Siberia%20cranes.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EGandhi%20was%20sceptical%20about%20the%20prospects%2C%20but%20later%20told%20Wright%20both%20countries%20had%20agreed%20to%20take%20protective%20measures.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EJairam%20Ramesh%2C%20an%20Indian%20policy%20adviser-turned-politician%2C%20says%20he%20%E2%80%9Cspent%20hours%E2%80%9D%20with%20Anne%20researching%20his%20book%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.co.uk%2FIndira-Gandhi-Nature-Jairam-Ramesh%2Fdp%2F8193355245%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9CIndira%20Gandhi%3A%20A%20Life%20in%20Nature%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fa%3E%20He%20writes%20that%20%E2%80%9Can%20ecstatic%20Anne%20Wright%E2%80%9D%20replied%20to%20the%20prime%20minister%2C%20and%20raised%20yet%20another%20subject%20%E2%80%93%20tapping%20a%20major%20river%2C%20the%20Teesta%20in%20north%20east%20India%20to%20save%20the%20Neora%20Valley.%20Gandhi%20later%20congratulated%20her%20on%20the%20work%20of%20World%20Wildlife%20Fund%20%E2%80%93%20India%2C%20of%20which%20Wright%20was%20a%20founder%20trustee%20in%201969.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20347px)%2085vw%2C%20347px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F31160811%2Fannetara-225x300.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22347%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F31160811%2Fannetara-225x300.jpeg%20225w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F31160811%2Fannetara-768x1024.jpeg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F31160811%2Fannetara.jpeg%20900w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-682723%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22463%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EAnne%20Wright.%20Photo%3A%20kiplingcamp.com%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EDasho%20Benji%20Dorji%2C%C2%A0cousin%20and%20advisor%20to%20the%20former%20king%20of%20Bhutan%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2FJigme_Singye_Wangchuck%5C%22%3EJigme%20Singye%20Wangchuck%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%C2%A0remembers%20how%20she%20encouraged%20him%20in%20the%201980s%20to%20save%20the%20habitat%20of%20rare%20black-necked%20cranes%20in%20the%20remote%20Bhutanese%20valley%20of%C2%A0Phobjikha%C2%A0that%20was%20threatened%20by%20plans%20to%20grow%20seed%20potatoes%20commercially.%20In%20Calcutta%2C%20says%20Dorji%2C%20he%20saw%20how%20%E2%80%9Ctraders%20in%20wild-life%20parts%20were%20terrified%20of%20her%20%E2%80%93%20she%20used%20to%20take%20the%20police%20and%20get%20them%20all%20arrested%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%20%3Cp%3EAnne%20Layard%20was%20born%20in%20Hampshire%20on%20June%2010%2C%201929%20into%20a%20privileged%20British%20colonial%20family%20who%20had%20served%20in%20India%20and%20Ceylon%20for%20two%20centuries.%20They%20also%20included%20Sir%20Henry%20Layard%20who%20discovered%20Nineveh%20in%20what%20is%20now%20Iraq.%20Her%20father%20retired%20as%20Chief%20Secretary%20of%20the%20Central%20Provinces%20in%201947%20and%20took%20on%20an%20advisory%20role%20as%20counsellor%20in%20the%20new%20UK%20High%20Commission%20in%20Delhi.%20That%20led%20her%20to%20a%20friendship%20with%20Pamela%2C%20Mountbatten%E2%80%99s%20daughter%2C%20one%20of%20many%20such%20illustrious%20connections%20%E2%80%93%20Mountbatten%20was%20in%20his%20final%20year%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHer%20early%20married%20life%20was%20spent%20in%20the%20social%20whirl%20of%20Calcutta%2C%20with%20her%20husband%20Bob%20who%20died%20in%202005.%20From%20their%20home%20in%20Calcutta%E2%80%99s%20prosperous%20area%20of%20Ballygunge%2C%20they%20became%20the%20centre%20of%20the%20energetic%20social%20life%20that%20the%20already%20dwindling%20British%20expatriate%20crowd%20continued%20through%20the%201950s%20and%201960s%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20political%20capital%20had%20moved%20to%20Delhi%20but%20Calcutta%2C%20now%20Kolkata%2C%20remained%20a%20boisterous%20business%20hub%20with%20a%20social%20life%20that%20drew%20royalty%20from%20neighbouring%20Bhutan%20and%20Nepal%20as%20well%20as%20maharajas%20and%20other%20dignitaries.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%20%3Cp%3EBob%20held%20senior%20posts%20in%20business%20and%20was%20involved%20in%20numerous%20charities%2C%20but%20is%20best%20remembered%20for%20managing%20from%201972%20to%201996%20the%20city%E2%80%99s%20famous%20Tollygunge%20Club%20and%20acting%20as%20the%20UK%E2%80%99s%20unofficial%20but%20influential%20consul%20in%20West%20Bengal.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20and%20Anne%20were%20part%20of%20the%20hunting%2C%20shooting%20and%20polo%20crowd%20and%20raised%20an%20orphaned%20tiger%20cub%20and%20leopard%20in%20their%20home%2C%20but%20this%20was%20the%20generation%20that%20put%20their%20guns%20down%20and%20campaigned%20to%20save%20them.%20Their%20daughter%20Belinda%20is%20known%20internationally%20as%20one%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20leading%20tiger%20conservationists%2C%20founding%20the%20Wildlife%20Protection%20Society%20of%20India%20(WPSI)%2C%20which%20she%20runs.%20All%20three%20have%20the%20rare%20if%20not%20unique%20family%20distinction%20of%20being%20honoured%20for%20their%20work%20%E2%80%93%20Bob%20Wright%20and%20Belinda%20with%20the%20Order%20of%20the%20British%20Empire%20(OBE)%20and%20Anne%20with%20the%20Most%20Excellent%20Order%20of%20the%20British%20Empire%20(MBE).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%201970%2C%20Anne%20Wright%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.telegraphindia.com%2Fmy-kolkata%2Fnews%2Ftiger-conservationist-anne-wright-passes-away%2Fcid%2F1971101%5C%22%3Ewrote%20an%20explosive%20article%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20exposed%20the%20illegal%20trade%20of%20tiger%20skins%20in%20a%20Calcutta%20market.%20One%20of%20the%20first%20detailed%20documentations%20of%20the%20large-scale%20slaughter%20of%20wild%20tigers%20and%20leopards%20in%20India.%20It%20was%20published%20locally%20and%20republished%20by%20the%20%3Cem%3ENew%20York%20Times%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3Ewith%20the%20headline%20%E2%80%9CDoom%20awaits%20tigers%20and%20leopards%20unless%20India%20acts%20swiftly%E2%80%9D%3Cem%3E%2C%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3Etriggering%20a%20series%20of%20reforms.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%201972%2C%20Anne%20Wright%20was%20appointed%20a%20member%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20elite%20Tiger%20Task%20Force%2C%20which%20produced%20a%20remarkable%20document%20titled%20%E2%80%9CProject%20Tiger%3B%20a%20planning%20proposal%20for%20the%20preservation%20of%20tiger%20in%20India.%E2%80%9D%20Launched%20the%20following%20year%2C%20initially%20with%20nine%20tiger%20reserves%2C%20this%20was%20the%20beginning%20of%20one%20of%20the%20most%20ambitious-ever%20wildlife%20conservation%20projects.%20She%20also%20worked%20on%20the%20drafting%20of%20the%20Wild%20Life%20(Protection)%20Act%20of%201972%2C%20and%20personally%20pushed%20through%20the%20creation%20of%20a%20number%20of%20protected%20areas.%20At%20the%20forefront%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20conservation%20movement%20for%20decades%2C%20Wright%20served%20on%20the%20Indian%20Board%20for%20Wildlife%20and%20seven%20state%20boards%20for%2019%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20conservationist%20wrote%20on%20Twitter%20(now%20X)%20last%20week%2C%20%E2%80%9DWe%20often%20speak%20of%20how%20hard%20it%20is%20to%20be%20a%20woman%20and%20be%20a%20wildlife%20conservationist%20in%20India.%20If%20it%E2%80%99s%20hard%20now%2C%20it%20was%20harder%20before%20us.%20Anne%20Wright%20tackled%20it%20all%20with%20courage%20and%20determination.%20And%20not%20the%20simple%20things%20%E2%80%93%20the%20tough%20ones%20of%20tackling%20poaching%2C%20building%20laws%2C%20and%20taking%20on%20illegal%20trade%E2%80%9D.%20Wright%20received%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sanctuarynaturefoundation.org%2Faward%2Fanne-wright%5C%22%3ESanctuary%20Asia%20Lifetime%20Service%20Award%C2%A0%3C%2Fa%3Ein%202013.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIf%20wildlife%20was%20her%20first%20priority%2C%20her%20other%20interest%20was%20horses.%20She%20played%20polo%2C%20competed%20in%20equestrian%20events%20and%20took%20up%20breeding%20thoroughbreds%20at%20her%20stud%20farm%20on%20the%20outskirts%20of%20Delhi.%20She%20kept%20her%20best%20for%20the%20Winter%20season%20of%202000-2001%2C%20where%20her%20mare%2C%20Fame%20Star%2C%20waltzed%20away%20with%20the%20Calcutta%20Gold%20Cup%20and%20The%20Indian%20Champion%20Cup.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EJon%20Ryan%2C%20a%20friend%20who%20took%20her%20to%20the%20secure%20stabling%20area%20at%20Royal%20Ascot%20to%20see%20the%20best%20thoroughbreds%20and%20talk%20to%20the%20stable%20staff%2C%20says%20%E2%80%9Cshe%20seemed%20to%20find%20that%20far%20more%20exciting%20than%20the%20grandeur%20and%20the%20pomp%20of%20the%20royal%20meeting%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%20%3Cp%3EKipling%20Camp%20was%20the%20first%20private%20wildlife%20resort%20in%20central%20India%20when%20it%20was%20opened%20in%201981%20by%20Bob%20and%20Anne%20%E2%80%93%20Rudyard%20Kipling%20featured%20the%20area%20in%20The%20Jungle%20Books%2C%20although%20he%20never%20actually%20went%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20has%20been%20the%20home%20for%20the%20past%2035%20years%20of%20Tara%2C%20an%20elephant%20made%20famous%20by%20Mark%20Shand%2C%20the%20late%20brother%20of%20King%20Charles%E2%80%99%20wife%20Queen%20Camilla%2C%20in%20his%20book%20%E2%80%9CTravels%20on%20My%20Elephant%E2%80%9D.%20Shand%20gifted%20Tara%20to%20the%20Wright%20family%20in%201988%20after%20his%20600-mile%20journey%20across%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20death%20of%20her%20husband%2C%20Anne%20lived%20partly%20in%20Delhi%2C%20where%20she%20was%20still%20breeding%20race%20horses%2C%20and%20Kipling%20Camp%20where%20she%20died.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EThere%20will%20no%20doubt%20be%20memorial%20services%20elsewhere%20that%20reflect%20her%20life%20and%20achievements%20but%2C%20the%20night%20following%20her%20death%2C%20after%20a%20brief%20Christian%20service%20in%20Hindi%2C%20she%20was%20cremated%20in%20a%20small%2C%20open-sided%20village%20cremation%20shed%20in%20the%20jungle%2C%20a%20few%20yards%20from%20the%20park%20alongside%20a%20burbling%20stream.%20Those%20present%2C%20says%20Belinda%2C%20included%20camp%20staff%2C%20past%20and%20present%2C%20local%20friends%20and%20villagers%20who%20knew%20her%20well%2C%20along%20with%20their%20two%20faithful%20dogs.%20%E2%80%9CAs%20we%20left%20the%20Camp%20there%20were%20alarm%20calls%20nearby%2C%20and%20the%20place%20was%20crowded%20with%20%3Cem%3Echeetal%3C%2Fem%3E%20deer%20when%20we%20returned%E2%80%9D.%20A%20suitable%20exit%20for%20such%20a%20courageous%20wildlife%20campaigner%20whose%20death%20marks%20the%20end%20of%20an%20era.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAnne%20Wright%20is%20survived%20by%20a%20son%20Rupert%20and%20his%20children%20Helena%20and%20Tim%2C%20and%20her%20daughter%20Belinda.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%20data-reader-unique-id%3D%5C%2264%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20originally%20published%20on%20the%20author%E2%80%99s%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fridingtheelephant.wordpress.com%2F2023%2F10%2F13%2Fthe-end-of-an-era-in-india-with-the-passing-of-a-wildlife-campaigner%2F%5C%22%3Eblog%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%20data-reader-unique-id%3D%5C%2264%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.thewire.in%2Fbyline%2Fvrbneo%5C%22%3EJohn%20Elliott%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0is%20a%20journalist.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698751819000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F31160638%2FCopy-of-Copy-of-Lead-image-size-2.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2F682699%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Wright%20was%20a%20member%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20elite%20Tiger%20Task%20Force%20and%20also%20worked%20on%20the%20drafting%20of%20the%20Wild%20Life%20(Protection)%20Act%20of%201972%20among%20other%20things.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2F682699%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22King%20and%20Queen%20land%20in%20Kenya%20for%20four-day%20visit%20as%20calls%20for%20apology%20grow%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698751680000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F10%2F768x432%2Fskynews-king-charles-kenya_6342622.jpg%3F20231031110247%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fking-charles-and-queen-camilla-land-in-kenya-as-calls-for-apology-grow-12997136%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20King%20and%20Queen%20have%20begun%20a%20four-day%20state%20visit%20to%20Kenya%2C%20which%20could%20be%20eclipsed%20by%20calls%20for%20an%20apology%20over%20abuses%20during%20British%20colonial%20rule.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A372%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fking-charles-and-queen-camilla-land-in-kenya-as-calls-for-apology-grow-12997136%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp